title: SEQ's futuristic 'inland freight port' takes first steps
text:
Topix › Pacific Travel › SEQ's futuristic 'inland freight port... SEQ's futuristic 'inland freight port' takes first steps 1 min ago Read more: Sydney Morning Herald 
Southeast Queensland's futuristic "inland port" - straddling the interstate rail line between Brisbane and Melbourne ports and allowing 15000 hectares for future industry - is about to become a reality. The inland port is at Bromelton - six kilometres west of Beaudesert - and part of the 15,000 hectare Bromelton State Development Area announced eight years ago in 2007.
